{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Inform disabled people of high success rate for PIP appeals at tribunal",
        "additional_details": "The latest full financial year data shows that in 2023/24 there were 46,803 PIP appeals cleared at tribunal hearings. Of these, 32,222 (69%) were decided in favour of the applicant.",
        "background": "We believe the Government should make it clear on the Personal Independence Payment (PIP) application form that 69% of people who appealed their PIP decision in 2023/24 won at a tribunal.",
